result.name: Shau Shau Shau Thai Food

reviews.text: I didn't eat thai food since many year ..and got a chance for meal after work with whole workmates last week..amazing dishes there ,food really delicious....the pork salad was the best.that was the second time I ate pork salad ,,love. The spice and not too salty mand soupalso nice too. Will get back again soon

Portion is quite big (tomyum soup, vermicelli salad and basil leave and minced meat noodles) and tastes quite authentic (and spicy!!) the stall does feel a bit less hygienic though.... (from the looks outside)...

Good food
Seats tight

Highly recommended Thai Food Rest.

Hot pot Fried Rice with Taro, Satay Skewers, Fried Vegetables with Chili, Raw Mango Salad with Filet Deep Fried Big Fish (For 2persons at least), Fried Spring Chicken Thai Style

Remember: Tell them less Chili or you can handle very hot Spicy.

Good choice
Toilets ok
Authentic Thai food, and you can go really spicy. My favorite Thai place in HK
Larb gai (minced chicken salad) was good, pork fried rice and crab fried rice were really terrible.

reviews.text: 地方狹窄，價錢合理，食物大致不錯
晚晚鬼殺咁嘈，快d執粒啦仆街 !
串燒勁唔得。湯粉絲唔知咩味，好奇怪。啤酒亦唔平，唔會再幫襯。
小店精神，味道誘人!!  廟街附近竟然有間勝價比高的泰式食店，雖然環境裝潢簡陋，但細看杯碗碟都整潔，食物味道豐富，不是單純於用添加味精，而且食材新鮮度彼高，價錢比例貼地，絕對可再嘗多幾次😎😘
